"{\n  \"correct\": \"no\",\n  \"explanation\": \"The `ax.legend()` call is incorrect because the `scatterplot` function does not automatically generate legend entries. The `legend` parameter in `scatterplot` is set to 'auto' by default, which means it will not create a legend unless there are semantic mappings (like `hue`, `size`, or `style`). Since no such mappings are provided in the `scatterplot` call, the legend will be empty.\",\n  \"patch\": \"8c8,9\\n<\\tax.legend()\\n---\\n>    # Add legend only if there are semantic mappings\\n>    if tips['total_bill'].nunique() > 1 or tips['tip'].nunique() > 1:\\n>        ax.legend()\\n\"\n}"